&lt;p&gt;Midwife - NIPE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen and we wish to appoint a motivated NIPE qualified Midwife with a special interest in Newborn Screening to support the NIPE lead midwife&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will include;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective running of the 7 day NIPE clinic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementation of practice change where required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in cascading training and training resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Involved in collating Quarterly and annual data such as Key Performance Indicators for submission to Public Health England&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring of the Newborn Infant Physical Examination (NIPE) failsafe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will consider flexible family friendly working hours. If you would like to find out more about this job role please contact Milica Redfearn 01183228936 or email milica.redfearn@royalberkshire.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMilica RedfearnEmail addressmilica.redfearn@royalberkshire.nhs.ukTelephone number01183228936&lt;/p&gt;
